   Here is the 52-48 roll call by which the
Senate Wednesday refused to delete curbs on nine semiautomatic
assault weapons from its omnibus crime bill.
   On this vote, a yes vote was a vote to delete the firearms
restrictions while a no vote was a vote to uphold the curbs.
   Voting yes were 12 Democrats and 36 Republicans.
   Voting no were 43 Democrats and 9 Republicans.
