   Here is the 50-49 roll call by which the
Senate Wednesday refused to reconsider its vote to delete curbs on
nine semiautomatic assault weapons from its omnibus crime bill.
   On this vote, a yes vote was a vote to reconsider while a no
vote was a vote to maintain the firearms restrictions as part of
the bill.
   Voting yes were 12 Democrats and 37 Republicans.
   Voting no were 43 Democrats and 7 Republicans.
   xxx stands for not voting.
